"hypothesis": "Objects in the grid vertically expand or stretch until reaching either the top or bottom of the grid while maintaining their original positions and other properties.",
"sub_hypotheses": [
"Level 1: Each object from the input grid repeats itself vertically staying within its initial column until reaching either the top or bottom of the grid.",
"Level 2: Each object maintains its original color, relationship with and relative position to other objects concerning column and proximity in the horizontal direction.",
"Level 3: When expanded, objects in a column from closer to the middle of the grid would usually reach the bottom while ones from the extremities normally reach for the top."
